    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Shanghai (
                        Cabot
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1510</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1510</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-06-24T23:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-06-24T23:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-24T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="1510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1510">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Colling, Guy Thomas: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-25T12:00:00+08:00">June 25, 1949—noon.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 25—4:02 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2488. [To Nanking:] Urtel 747, June 23.<note n="73" xml:id="d1510fn73">Same as
                        No. 1354 from Nanking, <ref target="#pg_1177">p. 1177</ref>.</note> Feeling
                    that it would not be wise call personally on Chang Han-fu for second time in 24
                        <pb facs="1194" n="1184" xml:id="pg_1184"/> hours, I am conveying your
                    message to him through Cheng Kang-chi (see mytel 1309, June 23, repeated
                    Department 2426). I expressed your thoughts to Chang Han-fu in slightly less
                    emphatic language in my interview Thursday.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 1349; repeated Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
